summary: Clean save without mods, completed Ustengrav, learned 3rd word of urelenting force, completed \"blade in the dark\", 1st level no points spent. With Dawnguard, Heartfire, Hi-res, and Dragonborn (final battle with Miraak must work). Game version 1.9.32.0
descriptionHtml:
This save was created for those who want begin new game but don\'t want complete annoying High Hrothgar and Ustengrav for 101th time. Stopped at \"Blade in the dark\" cause after this you can fully feel free. 
Another reason (for me at least) to create this save was to avoid quest bugs: final battle with Miraak that sometimes caused by using old save (game started before Dragonborn DLC), and bug with Delphine caused by unknown reason (probably by one of my mods).
Save info:
1st level, no points spent, default appearance, name \"Prisoner\", standing in Dragons Reach.
Somewhat increased \"destruction\" and \"onehanded\".
Quests were completed in \"speedrun mode\": with tgm, minimum dialogues, avoiding most combats.
Quest sequence: Ralof\'s side in Helgen, Bleakfalls Barrow started in Whiterun, not Riverwood (golden claw in inventory), Ustengrav \"speedrunned\" - word of power learned, Urgen\'s horn returned, 3rd power in \"unrelenting force\" learned, killed dragon in Kyns Grow. Killed \"cultists\" (can\'t avoid this :( ) - started \"dragonborn\".
Save was made on game version 1.9.32.0, russian, with Dawnguard, Heartfire, Hi-Res pack and Dragonborn DLCs activated, launched with SKSE. Save created with \"save\" console command.
Used some cosmetic mods (textures, meshes) but they actually have no influence on save file.

Installation:

Put file in My Documents\\My games\\Skyrim\\Saves
or
C:\\Users\\*username*\\Documents\\My games\\Skyrim\\Saves
author: Sersarge
